This paper discusses techniques for quantizing convolutional neural networks for efficient inference, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses benchmarking on CPUs and DSPs, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and hardware design (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper mentions quantization-aware training, which is a technique for improving the accuracy of quantized networks, and this falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
